      "author": "github-actions[bot]",
      "description": "## What changed\r\n\r\n- **Raised minimum Obsidian version to 1.10.2.** The Kanban view creates notes\r\n  through the Bases `createFileForView` API using a frontmatter processor that\r\n  pre-fills the first column's group-by property. That processor argument was\r\n  added in Obsidian 1.10.2, so 1.10.1 is no longer supported.\r\n- **Fixed column folder renames.** Board state is now updated before the column\r\n  folder is renamed on disk, preventing a stale-state mismatch when renaming a\r\n  column.\r\n- **Signed release assets.** `main.js` and `styles.css` now ship with GitHub\r\n  build provenance attestations.\r\n\r\n## Why\r\n\r\nThe version bump closes a latent runtime failure: users on 1.10.1 would have hit\r\nan error when creating a card from the board. The rename fix removes a\r\nstate/filesystem ordering bug. Attestations let installers verify these assets\r\nwere built from this repository.\r\n\r\n## Notes\r\n\r\n- Verify asset provenance with\r\n  `gh attestation verify main.js --repo jaidetree/obsidian-kanban-base`.",
